Interface FlowElement

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Group
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AggregateBy, AverageBy, BasePartitionTap, BaseTemplateTap, Checkpoint, Coerce, CoGroup, CountBy, DecoratorTap, Dfs, Discard, DistCacheTap, Each, ElementGraph.Extent, Every, FirstBy, GlobHfs, GroupBy, HashJoin, Hfs, Lfs, MaxBy, Merge, MinBy, MultiSinkTap, MultiSourceTap, Operator, PartitionTap, Pipe, Rename, Retain, SinkTap, SourceTap, Splice, SubAssembly, SumBy, Tap, TempHfs, TemplateTap, Unique

    public interface FlowElement
extends Serializable
    Interface FlowElement is a utility interface used internally to simplify DAG management. It is not intended for users to interact with these methods directly.
